                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/308.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="123" xml:id="d1419fn123">Similar telegram to the American Consul at
                        Tampico.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Spanish Ambassador, this city, by direction of his Sovereign, has requested the
                    Department to use its good offices to prevent Constitutionalists from enforcing
                    loan of 500,000 pesos demanded of Spaniards at Tampico.</p>
                <p>Bring to attention of Carranza, stating that this is done at request of
                    Ambassador and urge that no discriminatory or confiscatory action be taken
                    against Spaniards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
